name: Warung Sunda Rasa
address: Jl. Kesatrian No.16, Gianyar, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80511, Indonesia
review 1: Very tasty food, extremely affordable prices (between $1.50 to $3). You choose from the variety they have on display. The price changes if you eat certain types of fish. The only drawback is that they don't speak English, but it's not a big issue since you can communicate using Google Translate. Highly recommended.
review 2: Very good Warung. Delicious and fresh food. Everybody will find something for himself. Fish, tofu, rice, noodles, vegetables, sambal. Worth checking, not expensive. 25000Rup/person.
review 3: A place to eat in Gianyar City. Very cheap but clean and tasty food. I like pepes ikan and tahu. A favorite one.
review 4: Overall, this place is a good choice for you who like tasty food with nice seasoning. The price is quite affordable since you can choose what to eat. The service and place are nice.
review 5:
Fantastic, down-to-earth Sundanese cuisine - quite a rarity in Bali! Everything here is fresh and delicious, and all of it is very reasonably priced.
